        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_dyzǧ0yn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>dyzǧ˳yn</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>duzǧun</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>потрепанный</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>worn</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>исковерканный</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>distorted</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>dyzǧ˳yntæ kænyn</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>коверкать</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>distort</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>уродовать</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>deforn</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>рвать</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>rip</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>трепать</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>wear out</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>meǧæ… duzǧuntæj, mæstʒast, tartæj ærbacudæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>туча подошла бесформенная, мрачная, темная</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a cloud approached formless, gloomy, dark</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"
                            /><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*duž-gauna-</w></mentioned>. Для второй части см. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_q0yn"/> | %iǧun%i ‘шерсть’. Первая часть, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>duž-</w>
                        <gloss><q>дурной</q></gloss></mentioned> (в сложных словах), в современном
                    осетинском уже не осмысляется; ср. живое образование fyd-q˳yn | fud-ǧun [см.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydq0yn"/>] буквально „дурношерстный“,
                    ‘взъерошенный’. Древнеиранские сложные слова с %iduž-, duš%i- в первой части
                    многочисленны: <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>duž-manah-</w></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dušman</w>
                        <gloss><q>враг</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>duš-xvarəϑa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>дурная пища</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>duž-daenā-</w>
                        <gloss><q>следующий дурной религии</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w>duž-dōiϑra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>имеющий дурной глаз</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w>duž-vačah-</w>
                        <gloss><q>злоречивый</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. Ср. также <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dušman</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                        ><w>dusnām</w></mentioned> и др., <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>δuš-tuvān(δštw'n)</w>
                        <gloss><q>несчастный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>duš-darrau-</w>
                        <gloss><q>имеющий злую волю</q></gloss></mentioned>. Наряду с %iduz-ǧun%i
                    сохранилось другое сложное слово, составленное из тех же элементов, но в
                    обратном порядке (инверсия): %iǧuntʼuz%i(← %iǧun-duz%i) ‘хмурый’,
                    ‘взъерошенный’. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yn"/> | %iǧun%i, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_q0yntʼyz"/> | %iǧuntʼuz%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_fydq0yn"/> | %ifudǧun%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_zyǧ0mmæ"/> | %iusqummæ%i.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>233</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*duž-gauna-</w></mentioned>. For the second part see <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_q0yn"/> | %iǧun%i ‘hair’. The second part, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>duž-</w>
                        <gloss><q>bad</q></gloss></mentioned> (in compounds),is no longer
                    comprehended in modern Ossetic; cf. actual compound %ifyd-q˳yn%i | %ifud-ǧun%i
                    [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydq0yn"/>] literally “bad-haired”, ‘messy’.
                    Old Iranian compounds with %iduž-, duš%i- in the first part are numerous:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>duž-manah-</w></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dušman</w>
                        <gloss><q>enemy</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>duš-xvarəϑa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>bad food</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>duž-daenā-</w>
                        <gloss><q>following bad religion</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w>duž-dōiϑra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>having bad eye</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>duž-vačah-</w>
                        <gloss><q>evil-speaking</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. Cf. also <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dušman</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                        ><w>dusnām</w></mentioned> etc., <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>δuš-tuvān(δštw'n)</w>
                        <gloss><q>unlucky</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>duš-darrau-</w>
                        <gloss><q>having bad will</q></gloss></mentioned>. Apart from %iduz-ǧun%i,
                    there is another compound which has same elements but in an inverse order:
                    %iǧuntʼuz%i(← %iǧun-duz%i) ‘gloomy’, ‘messy’. Cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_q0yn"/> | %iǧun%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yntʼyz"/>
                    | %iǧuntʼuz%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydq0yn"/> | %ifudǧun%i, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_zyǧ0mmæ"/> | %iusqummæ%i.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>233</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
